        <h2>Common Issues with Cornelius Ice Machines</h2>
        <p>Like any commercial appliance, Cornelius ice machines require regular maintenance and professional repairs to keep them working efficiently. Common problems include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ice machine not making ice</strong> – Often caused by clogged water filters, faulty inlet valves, or a failing compressor.</li>
            <li><strong>Slow ice production</strong> – Due to low water pressure, dirty condenser coils, or a malfunctioning thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice machine leaking water</strong> – Can result from damaged hoses, improper drainage, or a broken pump.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice cubes are too small or misshapen</strong> – Usually caused by a malfunctioning water inlet valve or incorrect water flow.</li>
            <li><strong>Machine making excessive noise</strong> – Worn-out bearings, fan motor failure, or loose internal components.</li>
        </ul>
        
